                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Blah blah blah.  Don't look at wether it's tick based or spell based.  Don't look at how often it checks.  Look at ONE number.  that is the percent chance to work.  That is the ONLY thing that matters.  If it really is a 3-4% increase, it would be a 3-4% increase in out total DoT damage no matter HOW it's applied.<br /><br />Let's go into fantasy land here, for a moment, and pretend that our necro is doing 400 dps on a mob going balls to the walls with nothing but DoTs.  Let's say the necro is stacking 6 DoTs that do 400 damage a tick, last for 1 minute, and they are on 100% of the time.<br /><br />Let's also pretend that our wizard is also doing maximum dps, being 400, using nothing but nukes effected by crits.  Let's say the wizard is casting one spell that does 2400 damage every 6 seconds on the nose.<br /><br />Let's now add that the necro has a 25% chance to crit, per tick and the wizard has a 25% chance to crit per spell.  On average, the necro will have a crit tick (800 damage instead of 400 damage on that one tick for that one spell) 15 times per minute.  That is 6000 extra damage per minute.  Or, an extra 100 dps for a total of 500 dps.  25% increase, right?<br /><br />The wizard, however, will average 2.5 crit spells, for double damage, every minute.  Since their spell does 2400 damage, that would be 2.5 * 2400 or... *drum roll*... an extra 6000 damage per minute.  100 extra dps.  500 dps from our wizard with a 25% chance to crit on a nuke.<br /><br />But... what if our necro has a 25% chance to crit their DoT based on the SPELL and not the TICK?  Well, let's see.  They use 6 DoTs that last 1 minute each.  Each DoT does 400 damage a tick so each DoT does 4000 total damage, right?  With a 25% chance to crit on their dot, making it do 800 damage a tick for the full duration of the DoT... that means, per minute, they will average out to 1.5 crits.  Each DoT does 4000 damage so, what's 4000 * 1.5?  That's right.  6000 damage.  Or, 100 extra dps.  500 total dps.<br /><br />HOLY FUCKING COW!  You mean nothing matters but the % chance to crit!?  WOW!<br /><br />Now, per tick or per cast is a mater of personal taste.  In the long run, it'll average out to the same damage bonus.   Personally, I preffer per tick because it's more consistant.  The more skill checks you have in a given period of time, the more consistant your damage bonus is going to be for shorter periods.  That's why the turtle will beat the rabbit, right?  Also, wouldn't you just feel like a jerk if you got a crit horror off just to have some wizard crit SoS and have your duration cut off as the mob died?   I know it'd annoy me.  If it only runs for 4 ticks and one of those is a crit, I'd be a lot more satisfied than having 4 crit ticks and knowing there were more coming that I missed.<br /><br />Hope you people learned something and will better be able to judge the usefulness of the ability when solid numbers are released.</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
